ABUJA – Leader of the proscribed Islamic Movement in Nigeria, Ibrahim El-Zakzaky, and his wife, Zeenat, have returned to Nigeria from India. The Ethiopian airplane carrying the couple arrived the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport on Friday by exactly 12:01pm. The El-Zakzakys returned to Nigeria barely four days after they travelled to India for medical treatment on the order of the Kaduna State High Court. On their arrival at the hospital where treatment was expected to commence, the trip to the Asian country turned controversial. Vanguard gathered that they are currently in the VIP section of the Abuja airport with operatives of the Department of State Services, DSS, making effort to tale them to an unknown destination Recall that Ibrahim Musa, spokesman of the movement, had on Thursday broke the news of El-Zakzaky’s return. The leader of IMN, had traveled to India along with his wife for a medical treatment. The religious leader in an alleged video released on Thursday, said he was given the option of having his treatment at the hospital or return to Nigeria. Chinese investments in Nigeria reach $16bn – NNPC(Opens in a new browser tab) El-Zakzaky said that while weighing the options with his wife, unnamed officials stormed his room and asked them to prepare to go home. He had accused Buhari led government of frustrating his treatment in India.  El-Zakzaky had also accused the federal government of placing him under heavy security, noting that Kirikiri prison was better than the Indian hospital. In view of his allegations, IMN spokesman opined; “Following lack of a breakthrough in the impasse that ensued in the treatment in New Delhi of Sheikh Ibraheem Zakzaky, it is now confirmed that the Sheikh is on his way back to Abuja,” the statement read.<img class="size-full wp-image-1238584 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/el-zakzaky3.jpg?resize=640%2C361&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="361" srcset="https://i1.wp.